OL,5, Gary Lineker has said he will try to   
OL,6, keep speaking up for people with "no   
OL,7, voice", after criticism of his tweets  
OL,8, on the government's asylum policy.     
OL,10,FThe Match of the Day host had said the 
OL,11,Flanguage setting out the plan was "not 
OL,12,Fdissimilar to that used by Germany in  
OL,13,Fthe 30s".                              
OL,15,FHome Secretary Suella Braverman said   
OL,16,Fshe was disappointed by the remarks.   
OL,18,FThe BBC, which has impartiality        
OL,19,Fguidelines, said it was having a "frank
OL,20,Fconversation" with Lineker.            
